p: Gralinski and Menachery [ 12] illustrated the emergence and outbreak of COVID-19 in their study showing the timeline for the key COVID-19 events from December 31st, when the cluster of pneumonia cases was reported, until January 23rd. These events include isolating the virus, releasing the genomes, reporting positive cases among travelers from Wuhan, as well as reporting the new cases and deaths in China and globally.
